By Week 17, the pattern of the term had come into clearer view. Power was no longer only about what the president ordered in public, but about how the machinery beneath him was being rewired to serve a narrower set of interests and fears. Immigration, foreign money, and information control converged into a single story: a government that treated law as a flexible tool, citizenship as a graded privilege, and truth as something to be managed. The week\'92s events did not bring a single spectacular break. They thickened a web of practices that made arbitrary power easier to wield and harder to resist.\
